<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="quantitative_polymerase_chain_reaction_qpcr">Quantitative Polymerase Chain Reaction (qPCR)</a> - <a href="#quantitative">Quantitative</a> <a href="#polymerase_chain_reaction_pcr">PCR</a>. A method of determining the amount of a <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a> sequence of interest that is present in a sample. By monitoring the <a href="#amplification">amplification</a> of a strand of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a> during <a href="#polymerase_chain_reaction_pcr">PCR</a>, the original quantity can be <a href="#extrapolation">extrapolated</a>. qPCR can be used to monitor <a href="#geneExpression">gene expression</a> by <a href="#rtpcr">reverse transcribing</a> <a href="#rna">mRNA</a> into <a href="#rtpcr">cDNA</a> and then <a href="#quantitative">quantifying</a> the <a href="#cdna">cDNA</a> through qPCR.